cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use AtlasPI in academic work, please cite it as below."
title: "AtlasPI: A structured historical geographic database for AI agents"
abstract: >-
  AtlasPI is an open-source REST API and dataset of 747 historical
  geopolitical entities from 4500 BCE to 2024, with coordinates,
  GeoJSON boundaries, confidence scores, and 2,200+ academic sources.
  Designed to be consumed by AI agents and machine learning pipelines,
  it bridges the gap between fragmented geographic primary sources
  (Natural Earth, historical basemaps, Wikidata) and the structured,
  contextualized format required for automated historical reasoning.
  The dataset documents conquest, displacement, and contested
  borders without sanitization, applying an explicit ethical framework
  (transparency of uncertainty, no single version of history, no
  geographic or cultural bias).
authors:
